                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\"><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>!</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Mobile</placeName>\n                <date>August 27 1848</date>.</p>\n            <p>Your favour from <date>17<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> inst., with\n                acknowledgment<lb/> of the $20 00 in check on Pensilvan<add>?</add> Bank came\n                to<lb/> Hand. I have according your Request, inquired of<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. Bowlumet<add>?</add></persName> in Reference to the Books you send\n                in<lb/> his care for <persName>A Englander</persName>, he informs me that he\n                    for<lb/><sic>wardet</sic> the same to a <persName>Mr Pfister</persName>\n                Bookseller in <placeName>Montgome<lb/>ry</placeName> for deliverance, but as\n                    <persName>Mr Englander</persName> has left since<lb/>\n                <date>April</date> for <placeName>Germany</placeName> &amp; <persName>Mr\n                    Englander</persName> is at present absent<lb/> from\n                    <placeName>Montgomery</placeName>. I have instructed <persName>Mr H.\n                    Lehman</persName> from<lb/>\n                <persName>M.</persName> the Treasurer of the congregation to receive the Books<lb/>\n                from <persName>Mr Pfister</persName> or to deliver the same to all who may<lb/> want\n                any &amp; receive the money for the same. <persName>Mr De Silva</persName><lb/> says\n                that he hath written to you about the Books &amp; <sic>sayd</sic><lb/> something\n                about a Deduction on the same on account being<lb/> damaged. In Reference to those\n                Gent: who are in arrears for<lb/> the <sic>occident</sic> I will exert myself to\n                collect the money, but<lb/> I doubt if any will pay until they come here in Fall. I\n                shall<lb/> nevertheless write to them about it. The are all good &amp; will<lb/> pay\n                some Times.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have sold &amp; engaged all the Prayerbooks but <del>as</del>\n                I<lb/> have not rec. any payments, yet. I could sell probably several<lb/> copies\n                more say 6 or 8 of those c $2 50. if I hath them<lb/> here. If you mind to send any\n                you may do so, &amp; as <persName>Mr Y<lb/> Kayser</persName> probable sends out\n                some <add>?</add> to me, you could<lb/> without</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kk94z6n/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
